docs.lead_paragraph: Since the day he was sworn into office, President Trump has pursued policies and practiced politics with a single-minded focus on bedrock Republicans, showing little interest in appealing to independent voters. docs.abstract: The ugly story didn’t end with the abolition of slavery.
docs.snippet: The ugly story didn’t end with the abolition of slavery.
docs.lead_paragraph: When Trump campaign officials scheduled a rally in Tulsa, Okla., on June 19, they sent what looked like a signal of approval to white supremacists. For June 19 is Juneteenth, a day celebrated by African-Americans to mark the end of slavery. And Tulsa was the site of the 1921 race massacre, one of the deadliest incidents in the long, violent offensive to deny blacks the fruits of their hard-won freedom.

headline.main: Tulsa and the Many Sins of Racism
headline.print_headline: Tulsa and the Many Sins of Racism
